  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "This issue comes from [this comment](https://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/issues/2699#issuecomment-1141549195).\r\n\r\nIf the `paths.test` value does not correspond to an existing directory, Hardhat just shows a `0 passing` message. Since this is almost surely a user error, it would make sense to show a warning or throw an error (I'm inclined towards a warning).\r\n\r\nThe same check might make sense for other paths (like `sources`) but not for every path (it doesn't make sense for the `cache` and `artifacts` path). I think just doing it for the `test` path is enough, but I'll leave that open for now.",
